1PROVIDE CPVC CONDENSATE DRAIN WITH MINIMUM 2" DEEP SEAL TRAP, ONLY IF
EQUIPMENT IS NOT SUPPLIED WITH BUILT-IN TRAP SYSTEM. DRAIN SHALL EXTEND A
MINIMUM OF 3'-0" ON THE DOWNHILL SIDE OF THE UNIT. PROVIDE SPLASH BLOCK AT END
OF DRAIN LINE. CAP ALL UNUSED CONDENSATE DRAIN FITTINGS. TYPICAL ALL UNITS.
2ROUTE 2-1/2"Ø (10" WC) GAS LINE INTO BUILDING DIRECTLY OFF METER. ROUTE PIPE INSIDE
OF EXTERIOR WALL UP TO ABOVE THE CEILING.
3ROUTE 2"Ø GAS LINE THRU VERTICAL WALL ONTO ROOF. PROVIDE STORM COLLAR TO
ENSURE THAT PENETRATION IS WEATHER TIGHT.
4GAS PIPING SHALL BE INSTALLED ON ROOF EXCEPT WHERE NOTED, REFER TO ROOF PIPING
5ROUTE GAS LINE BELOW ROOF TO WATER HEATER.
6GAS METER AND REGULATOR ARE BY GAS COMPANY. CONTRACTOR SHALL VERIFY THAT GAS
METER ASSEMBLY IS REGULATED FOR 10" WC ON BUILDING SIDE OF ASSEMBLY AND HAS A
MINIMUM CAPACITY OF 712 MBH. GAS PIPING IS SIZED BASED ON 10" WC PRESSURE, A 0.5"
WC PRESSURE DROP AND A 250' DEVELOPED LENGTH PER TABLE 402.4(2) OF THE 2018
INTERNATIONAL FUEL AND GAS CODE. COORDINATE WITH LOCAL NATURAL GAS UTILITY
COMPANY FOR FINAL METER LOCATION AND UNDERGROUND GAS SERVICE PIPING
7PLUMBING VENT THRU ROOF. SEAL ROOF PENETRATION WEATHER TIGHT. VENT MUST BE A
MINIMUM OF 10' FROM ANY FRESH AIR INTAKE.
8CONCENTRIC VENT THRU ROOF FROM WATER HEATER. SEAL ROOF PENETRATION WEATHER
TIGHT. VENT MUST BE A MINIMUM OF 10' FROM ANY FRESH AIR INTAKE.
94"Ø RIGID METAL DRYER DUCT/VENT THRU ROOF WITH CAP VENT AND BACKDRAFT
DAMPER. INSTALL VENT WITH CAP VENT AND BACKDRAFT DAMPER. INSTALL VENT PER
MANUFACTURERS INSTALLATION MANUAL. REFER TO DETAIL ON SHEET M3.0
